text: Photosynthesis is the essential biological process by which green plants, algae, and some bacteria convert light energy from the sun into chemical energy (glucose). Using chlorophyll, plants transform carbon dioxide (CO2) and water (H2O) into oxygen (O2) and glucose, powering their growth and sustaining life on Earth. Smithsonian Science Education Center | +3

THEME: "CAMPUS CONNECTION" Create a Website for College Life Using Only HTML & CSS! Select ONE Problem Statement: Problem Statement 1: College Event Page ●​ Tech Fest, Cultural Festival, Diwali Celebration, Hackathon, Sports Day, College Annual Day etc. Problem Statement 2: Club Landing Page ●​ Coding Club, Cultural Club, Sports Club, E-sports Club, Music Club, Drama Club, Photography Club etc.

Hackathon Flow: 2:00 – 2:10 PM (10 mins) – Setup & Instructions ●​ Team registration confirmation ●​ Problem statement announcement ●​ Clarifying rules and questions ●​ Setting up your systems & files 2:10 – 4:10 PM (2 hours) – Creation Round ●​ Start building your webpage using HTML & CSS ●​ Work as a team and bring your ideas to life! 4:10 – 5:00 PM (Approx.) – Final Presentation Round ●​ Selected teams will present their projects to judges ●​ Explain your idea, design, and code briefly ●​ Judging based on creativity, design, and presentation WHAT YOU NEED TO BUILD: Using only HTML & CSS, create a website that includes: ●​ Homepage with navigation ●​ About section describing your chosen topic ●​ Contact/Registration form (design only - no functionality needed) ●​ Attractive layout and styling ●​ Animations (using CSS) ●​ Images and content organization

WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR: Judging Criteria: ●​ Creative Design & Layout (Visual appeal, uniqueness) ●​ Clean HTML Structure (Proper tags, organization) ●​ Beautiful CSS Styling (Colors, fonts, spacing, animations) ●​ Presentation Skills (Clear explanation, confidence) ●​ Teamwork (Collaboration, role distribution) Submission link: submit here PRESENTATION INSTRUCTIONS: Each presentation should cover (3-4 minutes): 1.​ Team Introduction (45 seconds) ●​ Introduce all team members (present and online) ●​ Explain each member's role and contribution 2.​ Project Idea (1 minute) ●​ Explain which problem statement you chose and why ●​ Describe your unique approach ●​ What problem are you solving for students? 3.​ Website Showcase (1-2 minutes) ●​ Demo your live website ●​ Explain key features and sections ●​ Showcase your design choices ●​ Highlight special CSS animations/effects 4.​ Challenges & Learning (45 seconds) ●​ What was the biggest challenge? ●​ What did you learn from this experience?
